  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PTM2.10.5">
<l>kaṟaivaḷarvēl karaṉmutalāk kavantaṉ vāli kaṇaiyoṉṟi nālmaṭiya vilaṅkai taṉṉuḷ</l>
<l>piṟaiyeyiṟṟu vāḷarakkar cēṉai yellām peruntakaiyō ṭuṭantuṇitta pemmāṉ ṟaṉṉai</l>
<l>maṟaivaḷarap pukaḻvaḷara māṭan tōṟum maṇṭapamoṇ toḷiyaṉaittum vāra mōta</l>
<l>ciṟaiyaṇainta poḻilaṇainta teṉṟal vīcum tirukkōva lūrataṉuḷ kaṇṭēṉ nāṉē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The great lord who cut down the entire army of sword[-bearing] demons</l>
<l rend="indent">with curved fangs along with [their] great worthy one in Lanka,</l>
<l>When, with a single arrow, first Khara with a bloodied, long spear,</l>
<l rend="indent">then Kabhanda and Vāli  perished,</l>
<l>I saw in Tirukkōvalūr where blows the south wind which brushes the groves</l>
<l rend="indent">which brush the [city] walls,</l>
<l>As Vedic recitations are chanted in pavilions on all the glimmering streets</l>
<l rend="indent">and in each house, as [the city’s] glory thrives since the Vedas thrive.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
